Saved!

HOW TO USE

LEADERBOARD TAB

The main view showing all players ranked by NET score (lowest first).

  • Tap a player to open their full scorecard
  • Score column: Shows NET score To Par
  • Color coding: Red/negative = under par (good), Black/positive = over par
  • Thru: Number of holes completed out of 18
  • Position: Players are ranked by lowest NET score
  • Click (gear icon, top left) to access Settings & Info tab
The leaderboard updates in real-time as you enter scores

COUNTBACK SYSTEM

When players are tied on the same NET score, countback determines the winner:

  • Step 1: Compare NET scores on the back 9 (holes 10-18)
  • Step 2: If still tied, compare last 6 holes (13-18)
  • Step 3: If still tied, compare last 3 holes (16-18)
  • Step 4: If still tied, compare the 18th hole only
  • Step 5: If still tied after all steps, players share the position
Countback uses NET scores (after handicap strokes applied) for each segment

PLAYERS TAB

Manage all tournament players and their handicaps.

  • Add Player: Enter name, handicap index, and tee color
  • Handicap Index: Your official handicap (e.g., 12.4)
  • Playing Handicap (HCP): Auto-calculated based on course slope/rating
  • Tee Selection: Choose which tees (White/Yellow/Red) player uses
  • Edit: Tap any player row to modify their details
  • Delete: Use the delete/trash icon to remove a player
Playing HCP = Handicap Index (Slope Rating 113) + (Course Rating - Par)

HANDICAP STROKES EXPLAINED

How strokes are allocated across holes:

  • Stroke Index (SI): Each hole has an SI from 1-18 (1 = hardest)
  • If HCP = 18: You get 1 stroke on every hole
  • If HCP = 10: You get 1 stroke on holes with SI 1-10
  • If HCP = 25: You get 2 strokes on SI 1-7, 1 stroke on rest
  • Net Score: Gross score minus allocated strokes for that hole
Dots () on scorecard show which holes receive strokes

SCORING A ROUND

How to enter and manage scores:

  • Open Scorecard: Tap player on Leaderboard
  • Enter Score: Tap hole number Enter gross score
  • Quick Entry: Use +/- buttons or type directly
  • Auto-Save: All scores save immediately
  • View Details: See gross, net, and points per hole
  • Front/Back 9: Subtotals shown for each nine

MATRIX TAB

Visual hole-by-hole comparison grid of all players.

  • Rows: Each player with their scores
  • Columns: Holes 1-18 plus totals
  • Color Coding:
  • Red = Birdie or better (under par)
  • Black = Par
  • Other = Over par (bogey+)
  • Scroll: Swipe horizontally to see all 18 holes
Great for comparing performance hole-by-hole between players

COMPS TAB (Competitions)

Create and manage team competitions with prizes.

  • Team Types Available:
  • Pairs (2 players)
  • Triples (3 players)
  • 4 Ball (4 players)
  • 6 Ball (6 players)
  • Auto Draw: Randomly assigns all players to teams
  • Manual Selection: Pick specific players for each team
  • Prize Amount: Set /$ value for winning team
  • Mark Winner: Click trophy icon to declare winner
  • Clubhouse Hole 19: Random raffle draw from all players
When you mark a winner with a prize, it auto-adds to the Winning Tracker!

TEAM SCORING

How team competitions are scored:

  • Best Ball: Best NET score from team counts per hole
  • Combined: Add up all team members' NET totals
  • Stableford Teams: Add all members' points together
  • Ties: Use countback on team combined scores

INFO TAB (Settings)

Configure course and tournament settings.

  • Course Name: Name of the golf course
  • Course Par: Total par for 18 holes (e.g., 72)
  • Slope Rating: Course difficulty (typically 55-155, standard 113)
  • Course Rating: Expected score for scratch golfer
  • Tee Settings: Configure par/slope/rating per tee color
  • Competition Name: Tournament title shown on leaderboard header
  • Hole Setup: Set par and stroke index for each hole

BACKUP & RESTORE

Save and load your tournament data.

  • Backup JSON: Downloads all data as a .json file
  • Restore JSON: Load a previously saved backup file
  • What's Saved: Players, scores, teams, competitions, settings
  • Reset All: Clears everything (use with caution!)
ALWAYS backup before making major changes or at end of each day!

WINNING TRACKER

Track prize pool and all winnings (found in Info tab).

  • Starting Pot: Enter total prize pool amount (e.g., 200)
  • Pot Breakdown: Shows Starting Deductions Remaining
  • Swindle Winners: Manually add daily swindle/side bet winners
  • Competition Winners: Auto-populated when you mark comp winners
  • Player Tracking: Shows cumulative winnings per player
  • Weekly Totals: Tracks same player wins across multiple weeks
Perfect for tracking who owes what at the end of a golf trip!

LIVE SYNC (Multiplayer Leaderboard)

Let everyone in your golf group see live score updates on their own device!

How It Works:

  • One person (the "Admin") enters all scores and uploads to cloud
  • Everyone else gets a link to view the live leaderboard
  • Players tap "Refresh" anytime to see the latest scores
  • No accounts needed - just a free GitHub token for the Admin

ADMIN SETUP (One-Time):

  • 1. Go to Info tab Live Sync section
  • 2. Click "Get GitHub Token" link Create free token with "gist" permission
  • 3. Copy token Paste in "GitHub Token" field Click "Save Token"
  • 4. Click " Upload Current Scores to Cloud"
  • 5. A Sync URL appears - share this link with your group!

FOR OTHER PLAYERS:

  • 1. Open the app on your phone/device
  • 2. Go to Info tab Live Sync section
  • 3. Paste the URL the Admin shared into "Sync URL" field
  • 4. Click " Save URL"
  • 5. Click " Refresh Leaderboard from Cloud" to see scores

DURING THE ROUND:

  • Admin: Enter scores normally Click "Upload" to push updates
  • Players: Tap "Refresh" anytime to pull latest scores
  • Upload after each hole or batch of updates - your choice!
This is NOT auto-sync - players must tap Refresh to see updates. That's what makes it free & simple with zero maintenance!
Only the Admin needs a GitHub token. Other players just need the shared URL!

GENERAL TIPS

  • Auto-Save: All data saves automatically to browser storage
  • Offline: Works without internet once loaded
  • Backup Often: Browser storage can be cleared - backup regularly!
  • This Popup: Drag by the header to move anywhere on screen
  • Multiple Devices: Use Backup/Restore to transfer between devices

COMMON QUESTIONS

  • Q: Why is my handicap different?
  • A: Playing HCP is adjusted for course difficulty (slope/rating)
  • Q: How do I fix a wrong score?
  • A: Tap player tap the hole re-enter correct score
  • Q: Where did my data go?
  • A: If browser was cleared, use Restore JSON with your backup
  • Q: How are ties broken?
  • A: Countback system - see "Countback System" section above
